headline: Capital One’s Brex Deal Is ‘Compelling.’ Why the Stock Is Falling Anyway.
summary: Capital One Financial  struck an agreement to acquire Brex, a fintech specializing in corporate credit cards, for nearly $5.2 billion.  The purchase price, consisting of a roughly 50/50 split between cash and stock, represents around 3.5% of Capital One’s market capitalization.  Jefferies analyst John Hecht noted that the acquisition supports Capital One’s aspirations in business payments.

content.title: Capital One’s Brex Deal Is ‘Compelling.’ Why the Stock Is Falling Anyway.

Jefferies analyst John Hecht noted that the acquisition supports Capital One’s aspirations in business payments.

headline: COF Q4 Deep Dive: Discover Integration Drives Growth Amid Efficiency and Investment Questions
summary: Financial services company Capital One (NYSE:COF) announced better-than-expected revenue in Q4 CY2025, with sales up 53.3% year on year to $15.62 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $3.86 per share was 6.8% below analysts’ consensus estimates.
